Dal makhani or dal makhni (pronounced daal ma-khaa-nee, 'buttery lentils') is a popular dish from the Punjab region of India and Pakistan. The primary ingredients are whole black lentil (urad), red kidney beans (rajma), butter and cream.

Panzanella [pantsaˈnɛlla] or panmolle [pamˈmɔlle] is a Tuscan salad of bread and tomatoes that is popular in the summer. It includes chunks of soaked stale bread and tomatoes, sometimes also onions and basil, dressed with olive oil and vinegar.
